    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> to the plate and press into the <strong>flour</strong> until evenly coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your<strong> crispy basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
