    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>to the pot with<strong> </strong>your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Bring to a boil and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the sauce begins to thickens – this is your <strong>creamy mustard sauce</strong></p>",
